[
  {
    "_doc": "Marunthagam Protocol Engine rules — v2 schema (2026-05-07).",
    "_schema_version": 2,
    "_design_notes": [
      "chief_complaint_pattern matches against the verbal_symptoms field ONLY.",
      "  This is the structured chief complaint extracted upstream. Matching",
      "  against the full Tamil narrative caused false positives in v1 (e.g.,",
      "  IMNCI-002 firing on a chemo case that *mentioned* the word fever).",
      "required_co_signals is a list of patterns; ALL must match somewhere in",
      "  (verbal_symptoms || tamil_question). Use to express AND-combinations",
      "  like 'chest pain AND (radiation OR dyspnea)'.",
      "negative_scoping is a list of patterns; rule does NOT fire if ANY match",
      "  in full text. Use for 'rule fires UNLESS narrative explicitly negates.'",
      "age_group: 'any' or pipe-separated set like 'adolescent|adult|elderly'.",
      "  Adolescent edge case (10-17): ADOLESCENT IS TREATED AS NON-PEDIATRIC",
      "  for ADULT-* rules (so ADULT-CARDIAC-001 fires on a 16yo with cardiac",
      "  pattern). Pediatric IMNCI-* rules use age_group='child' or 'infant'",
      "  which exclude adolescent. No overlap.",
      "duration_min_days / duration_max_days: integer or null."
    ],
    "_id": "_metadata"
  },

